<dl id="sa0982aw"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="sa" href="#sa0982aw">SA (VI.A) </a>: <a href="../../FF/fnbs/ssaall.htm#sa0982aw"> 982(aw)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> canopic,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There is at least one fine melodramatic situation (iii. 228); and marvellous feats of indecency, a practical joke which would occur only to the <mark>canopic</mark> mind (iii. 300-305), emphasise the recovery of her husband by that remarkable &ldquo;blackguard,&rdquo; the Lady Bud&uacute;r. <font color="green">[also x.195]</font>: From that time on and under the rule of the Ptolemies the morality gradually decayed; the <mark>Canopic</mark> orgies extended into private life and the debauchery of the men was equalled only by the depravity of the women. <small> Richard Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo; in <a name="RB01" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RB01"><cite title="source">1000 Nights and 1 Night</cite></a> (Denver, 1919) x.149</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
